      "text": "to provoke the eyes of his glory.",
      "verse": "13:8",
      "lineIndex": 38
    },
    {
      "start": 173.954,
      "end": 184.635,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "For Jerusalem is ruined, and Judah is fallen, because their tongue tongues and their doings are have been against the Lord, to provoke the eyes of his glory.",
      "verse": "13:8",
      "lineIndex": 39
    },
    {
      "start": 185.315,
      "end": 188.891,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "The show of their countenance doth witness against them,",
      "verse": "13:9",
      "lineIndex": 40
    },
    {
      "start": 189.071,
      "end": 193.251,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "and doth declare their sin to be even as Sodom,",
      "verse": "13:9",
      "lineIndex": 41
    },
    {
      "start": 193.431,
      "end": 195.149,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "and they cannot hide it.",
      "verse": "13:9",
      "lineIndex": 42
    },
    {
      "start": 195.329,
      "end": 197.094,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "Wo unto their souls,",
      "verse": "13:9",
      "lineIndex": 43
    },
    {
      "start": 197.274,
      "end": 200.571,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "for they have rewarded evil unto themselves!",
      "verse": "13:9",
      "lineIndex": 44
    },
    {
      "start": 200.751,
      "end": 216.819,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "The shew show of their countenance doth witness against them, and they doth declare their sin to be even as Sodom, and they cannot hide it. not. Woe Wo unto their soul! souls, for they have rewarded evil unto themselves!",
      "verse": "13:9",
      "lineIndex": 45
    },
    {
      "start": 217.499,
      "end": 219.264,
      "type": "line",
